    <node id="&quot;IMAGE_14&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The image is a simple, monochromatic icon featuring a stylized gas pump or fuel dispenser. The icon is rendered in shades of white and light gray against a solid black background. The main body of the pump is a vertical rectangle, with a smaller rectangular base at the bottom. Extending from the upper right side of the pump's body is a handle or nozzle, depicted with a slight curve and a distinct shape. Above the nozzle, at the top right corner of the pump, there is a small, rectangular shape resembling a sheet of paper or a flag, commonly associated with a receipt or a sign at a gas station. The overall design is clean and minimalist, clearly representing a fuel station or gasoline service."</data>
      <data key="d2">test_runs/test_mmrag_working\images\image_14.jpg</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;FUEL PUMP ICON&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
      <data key="d1">A stylized fuel pump icon, often depicted in black and white, signifies the availability of fuel or gasoline services. In the context of Yellowstone National Park, this icon is used on maps and service listings to indicate locations where fuel is available, such as Bridge Bay, Canyon, Fishing Bridge, Grant Village, Lake Village, Mammoth Hot Springs, Old Faithful, Roosevelt, and Tower Fall, as detailed in the park's service information.</data>
      <data key="d2">test_runs/test_mmrag_working\images\image_14.jpg</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMAGE_13&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The image is a small, square, monochrome icon. It features a black background with a white inner square border, and centrally placed within this white bordered area is a bold, black plus sign (+). The icon is simple and graphic, designed for clear symbolic representation. Given the context provided, which mentions 'Visitor Center or information station' and 'Full service', this icon likely represents a location offering full services or an information point, possibly on a map or guide."</data>
