    <node id="&quot;IMAGE_5&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The image is a black and white close-up photograph depicting a group of people, primarily adults and children, engaged in an outdoor activity. In the foreground, slightly to the left, is a young child with light-colored hair, possibly blonde, wearing a light-colored top. This child is looking towards the right with a curious expression. To the right of this child and slightly behind, another child with darker hair and glasses is visible, also looking towards the right. Dominating the central and right portions of the image is an adult wearing a light-colored ranger-style hat with a dark band. This adult's face is partially obscured by the hat brim, but they appear to be looking down and interacting with the children, suggesting a supervisory or educational role. Another adult figure is partially visible on the far right, with a forearm and hand visible, wearing a watch on the wrist. This adult also seems to be part of the interaction, possibly holding or assisting one of the children. The background is somewhat blurred but shows elements of an outdoor setting, including what appear to be wooden logs or structures, suggesting a park, camp, or natural environment. The overall atmosphere conveyed is one of positive interaction, possibly an educational program or recreational activity, with the adults engaging with the children in a natural setting."</data>
      <data key="d2">test_runs/test_mmrag_working\images\image_5.jpg</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;Park Ranger or Guide&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">An adult individual, likely a park ranger or guide, is depicted wearing a light-colored, wide-brimmed hat with a dark band, partially obscuring their face. They are looking down and interacting with children, possibly in the context of one of Yellowstone's educational programs like the Junior Ranger or Young Scientist programs, or providing guidance on safety, such as the importance of keeping children close in hazardous areas like hydrothermal features or near wildlife. The adult is also wearing a wristwatch on their left wrist.</data>
      <data key="d2">test_runs/test_mmrag_working\images\image_5.jpg</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;Child Visitor&quot;">
      <data key="d2">test_runs/test_mmrag_working\images\image_5.jpg</data>
      <data key="d1">A child with blonde hair, likely a visitor to Yellowstone National Park. The park emphasizes safety for children, advising parents to keep them close and educate them about hazards like hydrothermal areas, wildlife, and steep drop-offs. Children are also encouraged to participate in educational initiatives such as the Junior Ranger and Young Scientist programs, designed to foster understanding and involvement in Yellowstone.</data>
      <data key="d0">"UNKNOWN"</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A national park located in Wyoming that requires reservations for certain group sizes and RV campsites. It is also the location for contact addresses of Xanterra Parks and Resorts and the National Park Service."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is a federal recreation site where entrance fees are charged, offering various pass options, camping facilities, and subject to seasonal weather changes and visitor access reviews."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is a major national park in the US, providing various services and subject to specific road schedules and closures."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is a national park with specific regulations for visitors, including fishing, boating, and camping."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is an organization and a geographic location, providing visitor information, activities, and road schedules. It is the first national park in America."&lt;SEP&gt;"Yellowstone National Park is the primary location described in the trip planner, known for its high altitude, unpredictable weather, busy roads, dangerous hydrothermal features, and diverse wildlife."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-47639910c915bafe8d80a13752ccb8ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b3cdc79954b41510d5ae0999ef6daf3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c35ba44e693c85e6206ade502e115d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88e5c2ce20f231e3a806b09b6cab2c4d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e22ff6904de7a8eef70b8467d191a104&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7351b12b3e5ac87b530aa3bf02ecf8cc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;IMAGE_4_PERSON-0.JPG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"IMG"</data>
